Class fileReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • fileReader

  • public class fileReader
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a reader that redirects STD I/O to current directory and reads/writes files in current directory.

    • Constructor Detail

      • fileReader

        public fileReader(java.lang.String s)
        Constructs a reader that looks in current directory for the given filename. It also populates the list and set with file lines. Note: It skips empty lines. trims and lowerCase() all unempty lines.
        Parameters:
        filename - The name of file in current directory to read
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - throws Exception if cannot read filename
